## What Is Deferred (Out of Scope for v1)

The following are explicitly **not** implemented in v1. Do not add code, stubs, or partial implementations for these unless the spec is updated.

| Feature | Reason Deferred |
|---|---|
| **Mobile-specific layouts** | Responsive CSS via Tailwind breakpoints is sufficient for v1. Native mobile app or PWA work is out of scope. |
| **Animations and transitions** | Framer Motion or CSS keyframe animations are not added in v1. Static renders only. Simple hover states via Tailwind are acceptable. |
| **Accessibility (a11y) audit** | Semantic HTML and alt text on images are required baseline. Full WCAG 2.1 AA audit, screen reader testing, and focus management polish are deferred. |
| **Dark mode toggle** | The site uses a dark theme as Luis's default brand. A user-togglable light/dark mode switch is not built in v1. No `next-themes` or `prefers-color-scheme` switching logic. |
| **Analytics** | No tracking scripts, event logging, or third-party analytics integrations (e.g., Vercel Analytics, Plausible) in v1. |
| **Authentication / Admin panel** | No login flows, protected routes, or content management UI in v1. Auth context is stubbed at root layout only as an architectural placeholder. |
| **Blog or writing section** | Not in scope. No MDX, CMS, or content pipeline. |
| **Custom domain setup** | Deployment targeting Vercel default domain. Custom DNS configuration is out of scope. |
| **Complex error recovery** | No retry logic, offline detection, or error reporting services (e.g., Sentry) in v1. Surface the error message and stop. |